The session confirmed completion of Phase 3 of the phased migration cutover, with 100% of production traffic now routed to us-west-2. The production URL has shifted to https://app-prod-v2.us-west-2.example.com (v2 due to an API version bump that landed during shadow traffic). The us-east-1 cluster has been fully drained with zero traffic for 6 days and is awaiting teardown approval. A formal decision was made to tear down the east VPC on Friday, conditional on zero rollback events for one week from now.

The RAG service has reached general availability on the /v2/search endpoint, protected by a WAF rate-limit of 1000 rpm and now accessible to public users. P95 latency is currently 340ms. A new thread was opened for SOC 2 evidence collection, with Schellman selected as the auditor and a kickoff scheduled for next month. The evidence collection window starts now (T-30 days), covering access controls, encryption, change management, and BCP/DR.

The conversation included repeated confirmations of existing migration architecture details: Lambda functions continue to invoke the API Gateway endpoint transparently with 30s timeouts on cold-start paths, no VPC peering is needed (public S3 endpoints with bucket policies), cross-region replication remains asynchronous with ~200ms p95 lag, CDK is used for infrastructure deployment via lib/eks-stack.ts, integration tests run at ~85% line coverage against a dev account copy, and the shared NAT gateway cost optimization remains under review by Thomson in #infra. Secrets Manager replication is enabled with 60-second propagation, IRSA configuration works unchanged after adding the OIDC provider in the new account, and Route53 weighted routing handles DNS on the global api.example.com record with health checks attached.

